messages.name: Status
messages.description:
The `Status` type defines a logical error model that is suitable for
different programming environments, including REST APIs and RPC APIs.

fields.name: code
fields.description:
A simple error code that can be easily handled by the client. The
actual error code is defined by `google.rpc.Code`.

fields.name: reason
fields.description:
A developer-facing human-readable error message in English. It should
both explain the error and offer an actionable resolution to it.

fields.name: message
fields.description:
A developer-facing human-readable error message in English. It should
both explain the error and offer an actionable resolution to it.

messages.name: Pragma
messages.description:
The Pragma message represents a pragma directive in a Solidity source file.
A pragma directive provides instructions to the compiler about how to treat the source code (e.g., compiler version).

fields.name: id
fields.description: id is the unique identifier of the pragma directive.

fields.name: node_type
fields.description: node_type is the type of the node. For a Pragma, this is always NodeType_PRAGMA_DIRECTIVE.

fields.name: src
fields.description: src contains source information about the node, such as its line and column numbers in the source file.

fields.name: literals
fields.description:
literals is a repeated field of strings that represent the literals of the pragma directive.
For example, for the pragma directive "pragma solidity ^0.5.0;", the literals would
be ["solidity", "^", "0", ".", "5", ".", "0"].
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: text
fields.description: text is the text of the pragma directive.

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Retrieves transaction details based on chain_id and address.
The HTTP GET method is used, and the chain_id and address are passed as path parameters.

methods.name: Decompile
methods.description:
Decompiles the bytecode associated with a transaction.
The HTTP POST method is used, and the request body contains the transaction details.

messages.name: Src
messages.description: The Src message represents source information about an AST (Abstract Syntax Tree) node in a Solidity source file.

fields.name: id
fields.description: id is the unique identifier of the source information.

fields.name: line
fields.description: line is the line number in the source file where the AST node starts.

fields.name: column
fields.description: column is the column number in the source file where the AST node starts.

fields.name: start
fields.description: start is the character position in the source file where the AST node starts.

fields.name: end
fields.description: end is the character position in the source file where the AST node ends.

fields.name: length
fields.description: length is the length of the source code for the AST node. It is calculated as (end - start + 1).

fields.name: parent_index
fields.description: parent_index is the id of the parent AST node in the tree hierarchy.

messages.name: Contract
messages.description:
Contract represents a Solidity contract's ABI (Application Binary Interface) details.
In the Ethereum ecosystem, a contract's ABI is essential for encoding and decoding data 
to and from the contract. This Contract message encapsulates the methods that are part 
of the contract, allowing for a structured representation of the contract's functionalities.

fields.name: methods
fields.description:
A repeated field containing all the methods associated with the contract.
Each method is represented by the Method message, which details the method's name, 
input parameters, output parameters, and other relevant attributes.
fields.label: repeated

messages.name: Method
messages.description:
Method represents a contract function in the ABI.
It provides a structured representation of the function's attributes, 
such as its name, type, input parameters, and output parameters.

fields.name: components
fields.description: If the function has parameters of type 'struct' or 'tuple', this field contains its components.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: inputs
fields.description: The input parameters of the function.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: outputs
fields.description: The output parameters of the function.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the function.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of the method (always "function" for functions).

fields.name: stateMutability
fields.description: The state mutability of the function (e.g., pure, view, nonpayable, payable).

messages.name: MethodIO
messages.description:
MethodIO represents an input or output parameter of a contract method or event.
It provides a structured representation of the parameter's attributes, 
such as its name, type, and whether it's indexed (for events).

fields.name: indexed
fields.description: Indicates if the parameter is indexed. This is primarily used for event parameters.

fields.name: internalType
fields.description: Represents the internal Solidity type of the parameter.

fields.name: name
fields.description: The name of the parameter.

fields.name: type
fields.description: The type of the parameter, as represented in the ABI.

fields.name: components
fields.description: If the parameter is of type 'struct' or 'tuple', this field contains its components.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: stateMutability
fields.description: The state mutability of the function (e.g., pure, view, nonpayable, payable).

fields.name: inputs
fields.description: The input parameters of the function.
fields.label: repeated

fields.name: outputs
fields.description: The output parameters of the function.
fields.label: repeated

messages.name: Root
messages.description:
Root represents the root of a Solidity contract's ABI (Application Binary Interface).
The ABI is a critical component for interacting with contracts in Ethereum.
It is a representation of the contract's functions, the input and output parameters of these functions,
and details about the data types of these parameters.
The Root message encapsulates the main details of the ABI, including the entry contract's ID and name,
the total number of contracts, and a map of contract names to their corresponding Contract details.

fields.name: entryContractId
fields.description:
The unique identifier for the entry contract.
This ID is used as a reference to the main or primary contract within the ABI.

fields.name: entryContractName
fields.description:
The name of the entry contract.
This provides a human-readable identifier for the primary contract within the ABI.

fields.name: contractsCount
fields.description:
The total number of contracts present in the ABI.
This count includes the entry contract and any other contracts that are part of the ABI.

fields.name: contracts
fields.description:
A map that associates contract names with their corresponding Contract details.
The key is the name of the contract, and the value is the Contract message containing details about the contract's methods and other attributes.
fields.label: repeated

enums.name: OpCode
enums.description:
OpCode represents the set of operation codes (opcodes) used in the Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM).
These opcodes are fundamental instructions that the EVM executes.

values.name: STOP
values.description: STOP halts execution.

values.name: ADD
values.description: ADD performs addition operation.

values.name: MUL
values.description: MUL performs multiplication operation.

values.name: SUB
values.description: SUB performs subtraction operation.

values.name: DIV
values.description: DIV performs division operation.

values.name: SDIV
values.description: SDIV performs signed division operation.

values.name: MOD
values.description: MOD returns the remainder after division.

values.name: SMOD
values.description: SMOD returns the remainder after signed division.

values.name: ADDMOD
values.description: ADDMOD performs the modulo addition of two numbers.

values.name: MULMOD
values.description: MULMOD performs the modulo multiplication of two numbers.

values.name: EXP
values.description: EXP performs exponential operation.

values.name: SIGNEXTEND
values.description: SIGNEXTEND extends the sign bit to the left for a signed number.

values.name: LT
values.description: LT performs a less-than comparison.

values.name: GT
values.description: GT performs a greater-than comparison.

values.name: SLT
values.description: SLT performs a signed less-than comparison.

values.name: SGT
values.description: SGT performs a signed greater-than comparison.

values.name: EQ
values.description: EQ checks for equality between two values.

values.name: ISZERO
values.description: ISZERO checks if a given value is zero.

values.name: AND
values.description: AND performs a bitwise AND operation.

values.name: OR
values.description: OR performs a bitwise OR operation.

values.name: XOR
values.description: XOR performs a bitwise XOR operation.

values.name: NOT
values.description: NOT performs a bitwise NOT operation.

values.name: BYTE
values.description: BYTE returns the Nth byte of the input data.

values.name: SHL
values.description: SHL and SHR perform bitwise shift left and shift right operations, respectively.

values.name: KECCAK256
values.description: KECCAK256 computes the Keccak-256 hash of input data.

values.name: ADDRESS
values.description: ADDRESS returns the address of the current account.

values.name: BALANCE
values.description: BALANCE returns the balance of the given address.

values.name: ORIGIN
values.description: ORIGIN returns the address of the original sender of the transaction.

values.name: CALLER
values.description: CALLER returns the address of the account that initiated the call.

values.name: CALLVALUE
values.description: CALLVALUE returns the value passed with the call.

values.name: CALLDATALOAD
values.description: CALLDATALOAD loads a word of data from the call data.

values.name: CALLDATASIZE
values.description: CALLDATASIZE returns the size of the call data.

values.name: CALLDATACOPY
values.description: CALLDATACOPY copies a portion of the call data to memory.

values.name: CODESIZE
values.description: CODESIZE returns the size of the contract's code.

values.name: CODECOPY
values.description: CODECOPY copies a portion of the contract's code to memory.

values.name: GASPRICE
values.description: GASPRICE returns the gas price of the transaction.

values.name: EXTCODESIZE
values.description: EXTCODESIZE returns the size of the code at the given address.

values.name: EXTCODECOPY
values.description: EXTCODECOPY copies a portion of the code at the given address to memory.

values.name: RETURNDATASIZE
values.description: RETURNDATASIZE returns the size of the return data buffer.

values.name: RETURNDATACOPY
values.description: RETURNDATACOPY copies a portion of the return data buffer to memory.

values.name: EXTCODEHASH
values.description: EXTCODEHASH returns the hash of the code at the given address.

values.name: BLOCKHASH
values.description: BLOCKHASH returns the hash of a specific block.

values.name: COINBASE
values.description: COINBASE returns the address of the block's beneficiary.

values.name: TIMESTAMP
values.description: TIMESTAMP returns the timestamp of the current block.

values.name: NUMBER
values.description: NUMBER returns the block number of the current block.

values.name: DIFFICULTY
values.description: DIFFICULTY returns the difficulty of the current block.

values.name: GASLIMIT
values.description: GASLIMIT returns the gas limit of the current block.

values.name: CHAINID
values.description: CHAINID returns the chain ID of the current chain.

values.name: SELFBALANCE
values.description: SELFBALANCE returns the balance of the current contract.

values.name: BASEFEE
values.description: BASEFEE returns the base fee of the current block.

values.name: BLOBHASH
values.description: BLOBHASH returns the hash of the provided data.

values.name: POP
values.description: POP removes the top item from the stack.

values.name: MLOAD
values.description: MLOAD loads a word from memory.

values.name: MSTORE
values.description: MSTORE stores a word in memory.

values.name: MSTORE8
values.description: MSTORE8 stores a byte in memory.

values.name: SLOAD
values.description: SLOAD loads a word from storage.

values.name: SSTORE
values.description: SSTORE stores a word to storage.

values.name: JUMP
values.description: JUMP transfers control to a different part of the code.

values.name: JUMPI
values.description: JUMPI conditionally transfers control to a different part of the code.

values.name: PC
values.description: PC returns the program counter.

values.name: MSIZE
values.description: MSIZE returns the size of the active memory in bytes.

values.name: GAS
values.description: GAS returns the available gas.

values.name: JUMPDEST
values.description: JUMPDEST marks a destination for jumps within the code.

values.name: PUSH0
values.description: PUSH1-PUSH32 place the given number of bytes onto the stack.

values.name: DUP1
values.description: DUP1-DUP16 duplicate the Nth item from the stack.

values.name: SWAP1
values.description: SWAP1-SWAP16 swaps the top stack item with the Nth item.

values.name: LOG0
values.description: LOG0-LOG4 record a log entry.

values.name: TLOAD
values.description: TLOAD and TSTORE provide access to transaction-specific data.

values.name: CREATE
values.description: CREATE creates a new contract.

values.name: CALL
values.description: CALL invokes a message call to another contract.

values.name: CALLCODE
values.description: CALLCODE invokes a message call to another contract using the current code's context.

values.name: RETURN
values.description: RETURN halts execution and returns data from a contract.

values.name: DELEGATECALL
values.description: DELEGATECALL performs a message call to another contract, preserving the caller's context.

values.name: CREATE2
values.description: CREATE2 creates a new contract with a specified salt.

values.name: STATICCALL
values.description: STATICCALL performs a static message call to another contract.

values.name: REVERT
values.description: REVERT stops execution and reverts state changes.

values.name: INVALID
values.description: INVALID is an invalid opcode.

values.name: SELFDESTRUCT
values.description: SELFDESTRUCT destroys the current contract and sends remaining funds to an address.

messages.name: Instruction
messages.description: Define the "Instruction" message, which represents an Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) instruction.

fields.name: offset
fields.description:
The offset field indicates the position of the instruction in the bytecode.
It's an integer representing the position in the compiled smart contract.

fields.name: op_code
fields.description:
The op_code field is an instance of the OpCode enum.
It represents the specific operation that the instruction will execute.

fields.name: args
fields.description:
The args field is used to store any arguments or data associated with the instruction.
This field may hold immediate values or additional data required for certain operations.

fields.name: description
fields.description:
The description field is a human-readable string that provides a description of the instruction.
It helps developers understand the purpose of the instruction.

messages.name: Root
messages.description: Define the "Root" message, which serves as a container for a list of instructions.

fields.name: instructions
fields.description:
The instructions field is a repeated field that can contain multiple instances of the Instruction message.
It represents a collection of Ethereum Virtual Machine (EVM) instructions.
fields.label: repeated

methods.name: Get
methods.description:
Retrieves transaction details based on network_id and address.
The HTTP GET method is used, and the network_id and address are passed as path parameters.

methods.name: Decompile
methods.description:
Decompiles the bytecode associated with a transaction.
The HTTP POST method is used, and the request body contains the transaction details.

methods.name: GetHealth
methods.description:
Checks the health status of the opcode service.
The HTTP GET method is used, and the response provides health status details.

Uses variable-length encoding. Signed int value. These more efficiently encode negative numbers than regular int64s.
Always four bytes. More efficient than uint32 if values are often greater than 2^28.
Always eight bytes. More efficient than uint64 if values are often greater than 2^56.
A string must always contain UTF-8 encoded or 7-bit ASCII text.
